Title: Reproduction and Analysis of Boosting Margin Theory

Summary of Paper:
The paper proposes a refined theoretical explanation of boosting algorithms using equilibrium margin.

Reproduction Setup:
AdaBoost was implemented using decision tree stumps as base learners.

Dataset:
Iris dataset was used as a toy dataset.

Results:
The classifier achieved approximately 90–95% accuracy.

Ablation Study:
Reducing the number of estimators decreased accuracy.

Failure Mode:
The model performs poorly on noisy datasets.

Reflection:
Theoretical bounds were complex to implement but experiments helped understand boosting behavior.
